HEADWORD: Epizoön
<hw>Ep`i*zo"⟦oum⟧n</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Epizoa</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., fr.
Gr. <grk>'epi`</grk> upon + <grk>zw^,on</grk> animal.]</ety>
<fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>One of the artificial group of invertebrates
of various kinds, which live parasitically upon the exterior of other
animals; an ectozo⟦oum⟧n. Among them are the lice, ticks, many acari,
the lerneans, or fish lice, and other crustaceans.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

